===Impersonal love===
−
A person can be said to love a country, principle, or goal if they value it greatly and are deeply committed to it. Similarly compassionate outreach and volunteer workers love may be borne not of [[interpersonal love]], but impersonal love coupled with [[altruism]] and strong political convictions. People can also 'love' material objects, animals, or activities if they invest themselves in bonding their identity with that item. In these cases, if sexual passion is actually felt, it is typically considered abnormal or unhealthy, and called [[paraphilia]].
